    "body": "> Remove or ligthen the background pattern of the code examples. It looks very nice, but very disturbing when you actually try to read the code:\r\n\r\nWe should use the github scheme from [places](https://community.algolia.com/places/):\r\n![2016-12-14-162700_1013x295_scrot](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/123822/21187996/297413d0-c21a-11e6-89d0-e70beda2dc20.png)\r\n\r\nPlain readable, line numbers, you read this all day already on github (well BUT dark theme users omg @rayrutjes :D).\r\n\r\nAs for the other feedbacks I agree. Thoughts @LukyVj?\r\n\r\n(Thanks a lot @rayrutjes for this kind of detail killer issues)",
